


genfac3d(2)                    Scilab Function                    genfac3d(2)






NAME
  genfac3d - convert  3d datas to four sides facets

CALLING SEQUENCE
  [xx,yy,zz]=genfac3d(x,y,zmat [,mask])

PARAMETERS

  zmat           : matrix , zmat(i,j)= F(x(j),y(i))

  x              :x axis coordinates vector

  y              :y axis coordinates vector

  mask           : boolean optional matrix with same size as zmat used to
                 select entries of zmat to be represented by facets

  xx,yy,zz       :4xn  matrices. xx(:,i),yy(:,i),zz(:,i) are respectively the
                  x-axis,y-axis and z-axis coordinates of the ith facet

DESCRIPTION
  Converts 3d datas to facets representation

EXAMPLE
  t=(0:0.3:2*%pi)';
  zmat=sin(t)*cos(t');
  plot3d(t,t,zmat)
  [xx,yy,zz]=genfac3d(t,t,zmat);
  plot3d(xx,yy,zz)
  plot3d([xx xx],[yy yy],[zz 4+zz])

SEE ALSO
  plot3d, eval3dp.























